For his actions in Iraq he was awarded the [[Queen's Gallantry Medal]]. He retired from the MoD in January 2007 as the MoD<U+2019>s senior IED intelligence analyst and has since become a writer, broadcaster and the director of a counter-IED consultancy company.  Chris is also a Fellow of the Institute of Explosives Engineers, a Member of the International Association of Bomb Technicians and Investigators and a regular contributor to television, radio news and current affairs programmes.<ref>http://news.sky.com/home/uk-news/article/15926591 </ref><ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8646116.stm</ref><ref>http://uk.video.search.yahoo.com/video/play?ei=UTF-8&fr=yfp-t-702&fr2=tab-web&c=17&p=chris+hunter+bomb&vid=fcb922b1928178895de4e2fac4d6811f&dt=1310083200&l=139&turl=http%3A%2F%2Fts1.mm.bing.net%2Fvideos%2Fthumbnail.aspx%3Fq%3D5008203007590616%26id%3D04267c005e7fc7f3e6b841788a5742e0%26bid%3DWkQXExYmgPzziw%26bn%3DLargeThumb%26url%3Dhttp%253a%252f%252fwww.youtube.com%252fwatch%253fv%253d7MP4s55NPHg&rurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D7MP4s55NPHg&tit=Bomb+disposal+expert+opens+up+on+anniversary+of...&sigr=11a9nrp9f&newfp=1  </ref>  

[[File:Chris Hunter giving Motivational Speech.JPG|thumb|upright=0.56|Chris Hunter giving a Motivational Speech]]


Hunter presented the Military History Channel<U+2019>s acclaimed Bomb Hunters documentary<ref>http://theglobalherald.com/army-bomb-disposal-documentary-bomb-hunters-on-sky-531-and-virgin-236/17380/</ref> and was named as one of the top 5 Inspirational Speakers of 2011 by the JLA Speakers Agency.<ref>http://www.jla.co.uk/conference-speakers/chris-hunter </ref> In 2012 he was selected to be one of 15 Ambassadors for Prime Minister David Cameron<U+2019>s youth development initiative, the National Citizen Service.<ref> http://nationalcitizenservice.direct.gov.uk/ </ref>  

He is also a supporter and donator to numerous military charities including Help for Heroes, Veterans in Action, Tickets for Troops, Walking with the wounded, Combat Stress, The British Forces Foundation, Global Enduro and BLESMA for which he trained to run the 2009 London Marathon while wearing a complete bomb disposal suit,<ref>[http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/top-stories/2009/04/15/heavy-mettle-115875-21279588/ Iraq hero to run London Marathon in bomb disposal suit for comrades]</ref> completing it in 6hrs 56mins<ref>[http://www.justgiving.com/chrishunter4 Chris Hunter's Fundraising Page]</ref> - setting a new world record.


== Published work ==
Chris Hunter's first best-seller, ''Eight Lives Down'', was published in October 2007. It covers the four-month period he served as a Bomb Disposal Operator in Iraq.<ref>[http://www.rbooks.co.uk/product.aspx?id=0552155713 Eight Lives Down by Chris Hunter - Random House<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Its best-selling sequel, ''Extreme Risk''<ref>[http://www.rbooks.co.uk/product.aspx?id=0593060164 Extreme Risk - Random House]</ref> - published in May 2010 - charts the fascinating story of his journey into bomb disposal and the terrifying career he spent fighting the world<U+2019>s deadliest bomb-makers. [[File:Author Chris Hunter.jpg|thumb|Chris Hunter best-selling author of ''Eight Lives Down'', ''Extreme Risk'' and the ''Tripwire'' series.]]


Chris has also co-written two teenage novels with children<U+2019>s writer Steve Cole.<ref>http://www.stevecolebooks.co.uk/</ref><ref>http://www.amazon.co.uk/Tripwire-Steve-Cole/dp/0552560839</ref>  The first - Tripwire - was published in April 2012, and it<U+2019>s sequel, Deathwing was published in July 2011.<ref>http://www.amazon.co.uk/Tripwire-Deathwing-Steve-Cole/dp/0552560995</ref>


His name 'Chris Hunter' is a pseudonym.

